    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">繼承人</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">嗣</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>DESCENDENT who INHERITS something from someone.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most current general and neutral word referring to an heir is sì 嗣.</p>
<p>2. Dí 嫡 / 適 (ant. shù 庶 "offspring by a woman other than one's main wife") emphasises the legitimacy of the succession.</p>
<p>3. Hòu 後, zhòu 冑, and yìn 胤 are vague and include all offspring.</p>
<p>4. Tài zǐ 太子 refers specifically to the formally established and declared heir apparent to a king or an emperor.</p>
<p>5. Shì zǐ 世子 refers to the formally established and declared heir apparent of a duke, king or emperor.</p>
        </div>
